The reason behind this is that, without the intervention of the Americans, the act of independence by the Filipinos would seem impossible, since at that time, the Philippines is still under the control of Spain. At that time, there is no way the Filipinos can easily live independently from outside forces, that is why the Americans enabled them to incorporate and integrated smoothly into the world.

In order for us to say that there is nothing that is higher than the milestone of the creation of the government of the Philippines, the rest of all other triumphs is impossible to determine their significance in relation to this biggest event. Let us say that they are all equal, or there is nothing that is significantly greater.

Undoubtedly, most of these great achievements can be attributed to national heroes, whose are excellence in their field, but whatever these figures did, we cannot conclude that without the presence of the government in place, any of those may just have happened but would fail to survive and last. And those more recent accomplishments we have cited above, we would have failed to achieve all of them if it were not for the ability of the government to make necessary laws, investments and policies that can cater to the demands of the times.

At present, with all the advancements we now enjoy, our history that was already written in the past will become almost like an imagination the way we hear about Abram playing with his grandson, Isaac, after the latter’s mother died
